# ============================================================
# SECTION BB - M17 cycle outputs from cycles A + C (M3.25)
#
# Cycle A: studied GPT-5's reasoning text on M3.23 paired baseline.
# AIME-I-14 reasoning revealed GPT-5 used wrong volume formula for
# disphenoid (isosceles tetrahedron). Sanity check: GPT-5's formula
# V = (1/12)·√(2Σp²q² − Σp⁴) gives a²√3/12 on regular tetrahedron, not
# correct value a³/(6√2). Correct formula
# V = (1/(6√2))·√((p²+q²−r²)(p²−q²+r²)(−p²+q²+r²)) gives V = 160/3,
# leading to r = 20√21/63, m+n+p = 104 (= gold). GPT-5 propagated the
# wrong formula confidently; the voter caught the mismatch via cross-
# witness disagreement (smart_C had the correct formula). N=1 firing
# case so far.
#
# Cycle C: re-mined M3.11/M3.11b per-task variance. Headline
# ("wrapper 1.3-1.9× more expensive on average") averaged over a
# bimodal distribution: 4 of 10 hard-benchmark tasks had wrapper
# cheaper (0.72-0.94×); 0 of 10 easy-benchmark tasks. Pattern:
# wrapper's sub-step delegation amortizes vs baseline's full-frontier
# reasoning when the task is hard-multistep enough that baseline
# burns many reasoning tokens. Also caught: M3.11b headline said
# "both arms 100%" but h01-compound-percent had b=correct/w=wrong,
# so wrapper completion was 9/10 not 10/10.
# ============================================================

# Empirical claim — GPT-5 hallucinates class-specific formulas on
# specialized geometry problems; voter cross-witness mechanism catches
# this when at least one witness has the correct formula.
# Firing-case history:
#   N=1 (M3.23): AIME-I-14 disphenoid volume formula. GPT-5 used wrong
#     formula confidently; voter via cheap-pair disagreement → smart_C
#     tiebreak got the correct V = (1/(6√2))·√((p²+q²−r²)(p²−q²+r²)
#     (−p²+q²+r²)).
#   N=2 (M3.28 Q1): same disphenoid problem run through cheapcode-witness
#     v1x panel. Synthesizer caught cheap-a's discarded "/72" tentative
#     error AND surfaced 3 distinct derivation paths (Gram determinant,
#     corner-of-box, centered-box subtraction) — v1x output STRICTLY
#     richer than my single-pass Claude baseline (Q1 verdict).
# M3.35 lift 0.62 → 0.72 with N=2 grounded firings + atom-0011
# discipline (smallest distinguishing experiment honored both times).
claim obs_voter_does_not_catch_gpt5_formula_errors_falsified: Bool @>=0.99 = False
claim voter_catches_gpt5_class_specific_formula_errors_on_specialized_geometry: Bool @>=0.72 = not obs_voter_does_not_catch_gpt5_formula_errors_falsified
falsified_when obs_voter_does_not_catch_gpt5_formula_errors_falsified

